	year = {2020},
	abstract = {Example: Lur’e systems. When D = 0, the system (3.1) is equivalent to a nonlinear autonomous system ξk+1 = Aξk +B∆(Cξk), which is the so-called Lur’e system. Therefore, the sequences \{ξk\}, \{wk\}, and \{vk\} will be completely determined given an initial condition ξ0, and the feedback interconnection is well-posed. It is more difficult to analyze the internal stability of the nonlinear system ξk+1 = Aξk +B∆(Cξk) than the linear autonomous system ξk+1 = Aξk. The nonlinear map ∆ introduces some fundamental difficulty such that the spectral radius argument cannot be applied any more. If ∆ is a linear function, then the},
