	year = {2011},
	abstract = {Stefan.VanAelst@UGent.beAbstract: It is shown that bootstrap approximations of an estimatorwhich is based on a continuous operator from the set of Borel probabilitymeasures deﬁned on a compact metric space into a complete separablemetric space is stable in the sense of qualitative robustness. Supportvector machines based on shifted loss functions are treated as specialcases.Keywords and phrases:bootstrap, statistical machine learning, sta-bility, support vector machine, robustness.},
